To transform this sketch into a colorful website with the jokes replaced by two actual jokes, you can use the following HTML and JavaScript code:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My Joke Website</title>
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: lightblue;
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    h1 {
      color: red;
    }
    p {
      color: black;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
  <p>Really dumb jokes to make you laugh</p>
  <p>1. Why did the tomato turn red? Because it saw the salad dressing!</p>
  <p>2. Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field!</p>
</body>
</html>
```
This code creates a simple HTML page with a title, a heading, and two jokes. The background color is set to light blue, and the text is styled with a red heading and black text. The jokes are written in the body of the HTML, and they are displayed as two separate paragraphs.

To create a colorful and interactive website based on this design, you can use HTML and JavaScript. Here's a simple example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .container {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .box {
            background-color: white;
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            text-align: center;
        }
        .box h2 {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .box p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.5;
        }
        .button {
            background-color: blue;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 18px;
        }
        .button:hover {
            background-color: blue;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="box">
            <h2>Funny Joke</h2>
            <p>Push to reveal punchline?</p>
            <button>Push</button>
        </div>
        <div class="box">
            <h2>My Joke Website</h2>
            <p>Push to reveal punchline?</p>
            <button>Push</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```
JavaScript:
```javascript
const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.button');

buttons.forEach(button => {
    button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const punchline = document.querySelector('.punchline');
        if (punchline.style.display === 'none') {
            punchline.style.display = 'block';
        } else {
            punchline.style.display = 'none';
        }
    });
});
```
This code creates a simple website with two boxes, each containing a joke and a button. When the button is clicked, the punchline is either revealed or hidden. The website is designed to be colorful and interactive, making it more engaging for users.
